cept and write the `idle` value.\n   - When `cgroup2` is false (i.e., cgroup v1), after writing `cpu.shares`, add a new call to write the `idle` integer to the `cpu.idle` file.\n   - The OCI `LinuxCPU` struct already includes an `idle` field (since OCI spec PR #1136). The libocispec binding likely already parses it. The `crun_resources_cpu` struct in `cgroup-resources.h` should contain an `idle` field.\n\n2. **`src/libcrun/cgroup-resources.h`**:\n   - Ensure the internal `crun_resources_cpu` struct has an `idle` field (likely `unsigned long long idle` or `int idle`).\n\n3. **Optional: `src/libcrun/cgroup-internal.h`**:\n   - Add a helper macro or function for generating the cgroup v1 cpu.idle path if not already present.\n\n### Implementation Pattern (to follow existing code)\n\nThe existing code at line 828 in `cgroup-resources.c` does:\n```c\nret = write_file_and_check_controllers_at (cgroup2, dirfd_cpu, cgroup2 ? "cpu.weight" : "cpu.shares", fmt_buf, ...);\n```\nWe need to add after this (for cgroup v1):\n```c\nif (!cgroup2 && resources->cpu.idle != default_value) {\n    ret = write_cgroup_file (dirfd_cpu, "cpu.idle", fmt_buf_idle, len, err);\n}\n```\nWhere `fmt_buf_idle` contains the string `"1"` or `"0"` depending on the `idle` value.\n\nThe patch must ensure:\n- The `idle` value is parsed from the OCI spec into the internal representation.\n- The write is only performed on cgroup v1 (cgroup v2 via `cpu.weight.nice` is a different mechanism).\n- Graceful handling if the `cpu.idle` file does not exist (older kernels).\n\nThis set of changes will make crun support the `cpu.idle` setting on cgroup v1, resolving the differential behavior expected by the reproduction case.'}}, {'command_name': 'Plan.finish_current_task', 'args': {}}]
