. Check the clean baseline with `CONFIG=base_config.json bash repro.sh` when useful.\\n030|5. Compare exit code, stdout, stderr, and side effects against `expected_diff.txt`.\\n031|\\n032|## Result Validation\\n033|Payload: process args: [\"/bin/sh\", \"-c\", \"echo cpu-idle-876; cat /sys/fs/cgroup/cpu/cpu.idle 2>/dev/null || cat /sys/fs/cgroup/cpu.idle 2>/dev/null || true\"]; linux.resources.cpu: {\"shares\": 1024, \"idle\": 1}; linux.resources.devices: [{\"allow\": false, \"access\": \"rwm\"}]\\n034|\\n035|Oracle: Run the same buggy_config.json with a reference runtime and an affected runtime. A valid reproduction is a stable difference in exit status, stdout, stderr, runtime state, or documented side effects for the same OCI payload.\\n'\n",


